Infotact Internship Project-1
N-Map findings and mitigation strategies
Step 1:
Open VM and create tools of both Kali Linux and Metasploit by downloading the required installer from the web browser.

Step 2:
Nmap for scanning vulnerabilities for scripts (ensure nmap is installed):
-ifconfig
(Ensure network of both metasploit and KLinux are same)
List out the scripts using the below commands
-ls /usr/share/nmap/scripts/
-ls /usr/share/nmap/scripts/ | grep smb

Update the database of the scripts
-sudo nmap --script-updatedb

Pick a script and scan for the vulnerabilities:
-sudo nmap --script smb-vuln-ms17-010.nse <target ip(metaspl)>
-sudo nmap -sV --script vulners target ip.

-- After seening the vulnerability results of CVE scores:
Port scanning for the target machine without pinging:
-sudo nmap -Pn target ip.

Step 3:
Installation of OpenVAS:
-sudo apt install openvas(gvm)
-sudo gvm-setup
 Fixes for the system after scanning and CVE scores:
 -sudo apt update && sudo apt upgrade â€“y
